name:                \
stack:               ( -- )
return stack:        ( -- )
string stack:        ( -- )
contexts:            interpreting, compiling
category:
input stream:        whole line

decription:          read an discard all remaining input from input line, thereby
                     removing it from further interpretation. As consequence is
                     text from input treated a comment.

example:             \ this is a comment to end of line
                     : foo          \  this is a comment to end of line too
                         hello  ;

standard:            yes
                     https://forth-standard.org/standard/core/bs